    <section name="Maven">
      <p>
         CodeGist Common is a mavenized project that lives in the Maven Central repository. Given that your project is also mavenized, all you have to do is to declare a new dependency in your POM, as follow:
      </p>
      <source>
&lt;project&gt;
    ...
    &lt;dependencies&gt;
        ...
        &lt;dependency&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;org.codegist&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;codegist-common&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;version&gt;2.0.0-RC1&lt;/version&gt;
        &lt;/dependency&gt;
        ...
    &lt;/dependencies&gt;
    ...
&lt;/project&gt;
      </source>
    </section>

